<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7431> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7431" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Senator; see MRR 2.487. Shackleton Bailey has shown. that C. Albanius is the best attested spelling, both in the passages cited in MRR,, above, and in Cic. Att. 13.31.4 (CLF 2.173 and 461; Studies 6-7). See also Wiseman, NM 210, note 12. The name of Sestius' son should be read as L. Sestius P. f. Albanianus Quirinalis.[13x]\n" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/6829> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #6829" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/4> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Cic. Sest. 6; Fam. 13.8. Father-in-law of P. Sestius, so probably a senator for some time before 60." .
